# Ensure Domain Model Usage on Code

## Domain Specification Location

The domain specification MUST reside in [`docs/domain-specification.md`](../../docs/domain-specification.md).  
It MUST contain **"Ubiquitous Language"**. Also follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md).

Backend domain terms live in Passport and Visita `docs/domain-specification.md` — Backoffice UI must mirror those names.

## Pre-Change Checklist (Before Any Code Change)

1. **Read** the Backoffice domain specification (especially Ubiquitous Language).
2. **Question the change** — new screens, labels, service methods, or roles?
3. Update the specification **first** if shell or UI domain language changes.

**Do NOT write components or services until answered.**

## Coding Rules

TypeScript interfaces, service methods, component names, and template labels MUST use domain terms: **User**, **Profile**, **Role**, **Domain** — not `UserData`, `ItemList`, generic `Entity`.

Route paths and `*role` values must match [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) and Passport JWT groups.

## UI Elements Must Be Defined in Domain Terms

Button captions and menu labels (pt-BR) must appear in the Ubiquitous Language table or be added there in the same change.

## Testing Rules

Spec files should describe domain scenarios (`shouldHideDomainsMenuWithoutDomainsAdminRole`).

## Post-Change Update Rule

Update `docs/domain-specification.md` and [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) when routes, labels, or integrated APIs change.

## Violation Handling

Refactor technical names to domain terms when touching violating code.
